parts.markscheme:
Award **[2]** for each of two reasons explained, up to **[4]** marks total.

- **Targeted content / Relevance**; 
Clustering content into sub-graphs based on social tags allows the platform to provide highly relevant content to users <marks>1</marks>, improving the user experience by filtering out noise from unrelated topics <marks>1</marks>

- **Computational efficiency**; 
Search and recommendation algorithms are much faster when restricted to a smaller sub-graph than when processing the entire global web graph <marks>1</marks>, which allows for real-time content updates and lower latency <marks>1</marks>

- **Improved visualization and navigation**; 
Displaying a sub-graph allows users to see the most important nodes and relationships within a specific niche <marks>1</marks>, making it easier to identify key trends or influencers without the clutter of unrelated data <marks>1</marks>

Award **[2]** for one limitation described.

- **Creation of filter bubbles / lack of diversity**; 
Users may only be exposed to content within their specific sub-graph <marks>1</marks>, which prevents them from encountering diverse perspectives or discovering unrelated but potentially interesting new topics <marks>1</marks>

- **Exclusion of weakly linked nodes**; 
Some relevant web pages may be excluded from a sub-graph if they are only loosely connected to the main cluster <marks>1</marks>, resulting in the user seeing an incomplete or biased representation of the topic <marks>1</marks>
